    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hold on, something isn't adding up. You just said you're the seller and you're ready to sign the PO? That's not how this works. You're buying the steel from me. \n\nAlso, if you're so worried about the market shifting and need to lock this in, why are you pushing back on the price? Usually, when someone is in a \"rush\" like you're claiming, they're willing to pay a premium to ensure they don't run out. If you're actually in a bind, you'd be asking me for a bulk discount to make the quick turnaround worth it for your company. Are you sure you actually need this by tomorrow, or are you just playing games?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
